The defendant Raymond R Crabb was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Raymond R Crabb is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Raymond R Crabb was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse - Infliction of Physical Pain or Injury], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Case called at 1:58 pm [Clerk SH]
[Reserve Judge Robert Mawdsley presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Raymond R Crabb in court with Attorney Jordan Lippert. ADA Jeffrey Martin Shock appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
ADA Shock informs the Court that they received no correspondence from the victim
Atty Lippert informs the Court that victim is present, did speak with her prior to the hearing and she indicated that she does not wish to make any statments

Constitutional rights given; plea of "Guilty" entered on Count #3; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.
On Motion of the State, the Court dismisses outright Counts #1 and #2

On Count #3, the Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 1 year, with conditions:
--AODA Assessment & Follow Through with any recommended treatment, per Agent
--To undergo any other type of assessment, treatment or counseling as required per Agent
--No possession of any dangerous weapon
--Anger Management Counseling
--No acts or threats of violence
--No possession or consumption of alcohol
--No presence in bars, taverns or liquor stores
--To pay statutory costs of $243
--To pay $100 domestic abuse surcharge
--To pay $200 DNA Surcharge
--To submit DNA Sample upon demand
